== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick
pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter
@lemon{1}.

Trim green beans if necessary or trim and halve @?Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}
lengthwise. (Save carrots for another use.)

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Swap in green beans or Brussels sprouts for carrots. Roast 10-12 minutes
> for green beans or 15-20 minutes for Brussels sprouts.

== Garlic Couscous ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce}, half the garlic, and a big pinch of
salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until couscous is toasted and garlic is
fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1} and 3⁄4 cup water. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce heat to low. Cook couscous until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Salmon ==

While couscous cooks, pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick,
#stainless steel pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon to pan, skin sides
down. Cook salmon until skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat;
transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Lemon-Dijon Sauce ==

Dice @butter{2%TBSP} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, 1 TBSP water, 1 tsp sugar,
juice from two lemon wedges, and as much lemon zest as you like.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for salmon over medium heat. Add
remaining garlic and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in mustard mixture. Add diced butter one piece at a time, whisking
constantly, until butter has melted and sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== To Serve ==

Stir @butter{1/2%TBSP} into pot with couscous until melted. Taste and season
with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide couscous and carrots between plates in separate sections. Top couscous
with salmon and drizzle salmon with lemon-Dijon sauce. Serve with a squeeze
of lemon juice and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.